Robert Blake faced accusations of killing his wife, Bonny Lee Bakley, with the prosecution arguing that he wanted her dead after failed attempts to solicit others.
Witnesses highlighted his desire to keep their baby, Rosie, despite his troubled relationship with Bakley.
The defense emphasized doubts about the prosecution's witnesses, including the portrayal of Bakley as a grifter.
Humor was used in the courtroom, but the focus remained on the serious allegations against Blake.
The trial showcased a mix of drama and absurdity, leaving jurors to determine Blake's fate in a case filled with twists and turns.
